column3:
It's a little unclear why the construction of the `CScript` here is different from the other two `CHECK`s in the same test, does this change in construction test the correctness of `IsExpectedWitnessProgram` in any way? As in, what advantages does this have over:

```c++
wit.clear();
program.resize(30);
wit << OP_5 << program;
BOOST_CHECK(IsExpectedWitnessProgram(wit, 5, program));
`

```suggestion
    // Witness programs have a minimum data push of 2 bytes
    std::vector<unsigned char> program = {42, 18};
```

```suggestion
    // Witness programs have a maximum data push of 40 bytes
    program.resize(40);
```
